    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is a Life Path Number?</summary>
        <p>A Life Path Number is a single-digit number (1 through 9) or Master Number (11, 22, or 33) derived from your full date of birth. In numerology, it is considered the most important number in your personal chart because it is said to represent your core personality traits, natural strengths, key challenges, and overall life purpose. It is calculated by reducing your birth month, day, and year to individual digits and then summing them.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I calculate my Life Path Number?</summary>
        <p>Break your birthday into three parts: month, day, and year. Reduce each part to a single digit by adding its digits together (for example, 15 becomes 1 + 5 = 6). Then add the three single digits together and reduce once more. If at any step you get 11, 22, or 33, stop reducing, as those are Master Numbers. For a quick answer, use our <a href="/astrology-calculators/numerology-calculator/">numerology calculator</a> to get your result instantly.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are Master Numbers in numerology?</summary>
        <p>Master Numbers are 11, 22, and 33. Unlike other double-digit results, they are not reduced to a single digit because they are believed to carry intensified spiritual significance and heightened potential. The 11 amplifies intuition, the 22 amplifies practical vision, and the 33 amplifies compassion and teaching ability. Having a Master Number does not make someone superior; it suggests a path with both greater potential and greater internal pressure.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can two people with the same Life Path Number have different personalities?</summary>
        <p>Absolutely. A Life Path Number describes broad themes and tendencies, not a fixed personality type. Two people who are both Life Path 4s might express that builder energy in completely different ways depending on their upbringing, culture, life experiences, and personal choices. Numerology is a framework for self-reflection, not a deterministic system. It highlights patterns and possibilities, but it does not define who you are.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is numerology scientifically proven?</summary>
        <p>No. Numerology has no empirical scientific evidence supporting its claims. It is a centuries-old metaphysical tradition rooted in the belief that numbers carry symbolic meaning. Many people find it useful as a tool for introspection and personal growth, but it should be treated as entertainment and self-reflection rather than fact. It should never be used as the basis for medical, financial, or legal decisions.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

